{
  "texts": [
    "After training, we analyze top-activating instances and timesteps per SAE neuron, forming hypotheses about semantically meaningful features in the model's internal representations.",
    "Experimental SetupOur classifier f θ operates on inputs X ∈ R T ×C, where T = 25 is the sequence length and C = 12 is the number of channels.",
    "We use d to denote the model embedding (hidden) dimension used by the convolutional front end, positional embeddings, attention blocks, and MLPs; L the number of encoder layers; H the number of attention heads per layer; and K the number of target classes.",
    "The model consists of:1.",
    "Convolutional front end: Three 1D convolutional layers with kernel sizes 5, 3, 3 and hidden-dimensional transitions C → d/4, d/4 → d/2, d/2 → d, each followed by batch-normalization and ReLU. 2."
  ]
}